<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,655,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Remarks</emphasis>
. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel, C. E." box="[357,539,654,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" pagination="177 - 307" refId="ref2434" refString="Mickel, C. E. (1935) The mutillid wasps of the islands of the Pacific Ocean (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 83 (2), 177 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1935. tb 01207. x" type="journal article" year="1935">Mickel’s (1935)</bibRefCitation>
key to the females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1899" box="[803,889,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Timulla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[803,889,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Timulla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species keys to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zavattari" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[1137,1430,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Petersenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macassarica">
<emphasis box="[1137,1430,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Petersenidia macassarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, having T2 with a high, median longitudinal carina on the basal half (by this character the new species and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zavattari" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Petersenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macassarica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">P. macassarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from other congeners), but the new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zavattari" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[914,1082,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Petersenidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macassarica">
<emphasis box="[914,1082,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">P. macassarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the much shorter and smaller carina on T2, the lack of a posterior interrupted pale fringe on T2 and the smooth pygidium.
</paragraph>
